   1  #!/usr/bin/env python 
   2  """ 
   3  Statstical analysis of the presynaptic terminal. 
   4   
   5  Common usage contains the following steps: 
   6   
   7  1) Make structure specific pickles. These pickles contain data from all  
   8  individual segmentation & analysis pickles. This step needs to be executed  
   9  only when a new individual segmentation & analysis pickle is added. 
  10   
  11    - Make catalog files for all datasets in ../catalog/ 
  12    - Copy this script to a desired directory and (optionally) rename it to  
  13      work.py  
  14    - Adjust parameters in this script 
  15    - cd to this script directory, then in ipython (or similar) execute: 
  16        > import work 
  17        > from work import * 
  18        > work.main(individual=True, save=True) 
  19   
  20    This should create few pickle files in this directory (tethers.pkl,  
  21    sv.pkl, ...) 
  22   
  23  2) Create profile in order to keep profile-specific history. Not required,  
  24  can be used only in IPython qtconsole before it became Jupyter and doesn't  
  25  work with Jupyter. Need to be done only once. 
  26    
  27    - Create ipython profile for your project:  
  28        $ ipython profile create <project_name> 
  29    - Create startup file for this profile, it enough to have: 
  30        import work 
  31        work.main() 
  32        from work import * 
  33   
  34  3a) Statistical analysis in Jupyter notebook or qtconsole (current way) 
  35   
  36    - Start jupyter notebook or qtconsole 
  37    - Setup plotting (in notebook /  qtconsole): 
  38        %matplotlib inline 
  39    - Load and preprocess structure dependent pickles (in notebook / qtconsole): 
  40        import work 
  41        work.main() 
  42        from work import *  
  43    - Copy desired individual analysis commands from this script (see SV  
  44    distribution and the following sections), paste them in the notebook / 
  45    qtconsole and execute  
  46    - Save notebook 
  47   
  48  3b) Statistical analysis in IPython qtconsole (used before Jupyter) 
  49   
  50    - Start ipython (qtconsole is optional, profile only if created): 
  51        $ ipython qtconsole  --profile=project_name --pylab=qt 
  52    - In ipython (not needed if profile used): 
  53        > import work 
  54        > work.main() 
  55        > from work import * 
  56    - Run individual analysis commands (from SV distribution section and below) 
  57   
  58    - If work.py is edited during an ipython session: 
  59        > reload(work) 
  60        > from work import *

 542 -def stats( 
 543          data, name, bins=None, bin_names=None, fraction=None, join=None,  
 544          groups=None, identifiers=None, test=None, reference=None, ddof=1,  
 545          out=sys.stdout, label=None, outNames=None, plot_=True, plot_name=None, 
 546          yerr='sem', plot_type='bar', randomized_x=False, confidence='stars', 
 547          title='', x_label=None, y_label=None): 

 548      """ 
 549      Does statistical analysis of data specified by args data and name, prints 
 550      and plots the results as a bar chart. 
 551   
 552      Argument join determines how the data is pooled across experiments. 
 553      If join is 'join', data of individual experiments (observations) are  
 554      joined (pooled)  together within a group to be used for further  
 555      analysis. If it is 'mean', the mean value for each experiment is  
 556      calculated and these means are used for further analysis. 
 557   
 558      Argument bins determined how the above obtained data is further  
 559      processed. If arg bins is not specified, basic stats (mean, std, sem) 
 560      are calculated for all groups and the data is statistically compared  
 561      among the groups.  
 562   
 563      Alternatively, if arg bins is specified, histograms of the data are  
 564      calculated for all groups (property name 'histogram'). Histograms are  
 565      normalized to 1 to get probabilities (property name 'probability'). The  
 566      probability for bin indexed by arg fraction is saved separately as  
 567      property 'fraction'. For example, fraction of connected vesicles is  
 568      obtained for name='n_connection', bins=[0,1,100], fraction=1. The  
 569      histograms are statistically compared between groups. 
 570   
 571      Joins 'join_bins' and 'byIndex' are described below. Specifically, 
 572      the following types of analysis are implemented:  
 573   
 574        - join is None: a value is printed and a bar is plotted for each  
 575        experiment. This value is either the value of the specified property if  
 576        scalar, or a mean of the property values if indexed. If the data is  
 577        indexed, both significance between groups and between experiments  
 578        are calculated. 
 579   
 580        - join='join', bins=None: Data is pooled across experiments of 
 581        the same group, basic stats are calculated within groups and  
 582        statistically compared between groups. 
 583   
 584        - join='join', bins specified (not None): Data is pooled across  
 585        experiments of the same group, histograms (acording to arg bins) 
 586        of the data values are calculated within group and statistically  
 587        compared among groups. 
 588   
 589        - join='mean', bins=None: Mean values are calculated for all 
 590        experiments, basic stats are calculated for means within groups  
 591        and statistically compared between groups. 
 592   
 593        - join='mean', bins specified (not None): Mean values are  
 594        calculated for all experiment, histograms (acording to arg bins) 
 595        of the means are calculated within groups and statistically  
 596        compared between groups. 
 597   
 598        - join='mean_bin', bins have to be specified (not None):  
 599        Histograms of the data values are calculated for each experiment  
 600        (acording to arg bins) and normalized to 1, basic stats are  
 601        calculated for values of the bin specified by arg within groups,  
 602        and statistically compared between groups 
 603       
 604        - join='byIndex', bins should not be specified: Basic stats  
 605        (mean, std, sem) are calculated for each index (position)  
 606        separately. Data has to be indexed, and all experiments within  
 607        one group have to have same ids. 
 608   
 609      If specified, args groups and identifiers specify the order of groups 
 610      and experiments on the x axis.  
 611   
 612      Arg plot_name specifies which statistical property to plot. If it is not  
 613      specified the property to plot is determined in the following way: if arg 
 614      bins are not given 'mean' is plotted, otherwise if bin_names is specified 
 615      'histogram' is plotted and 'fraction' in case bin_names is not specified.  
 616      Therefore, most often arg plot_name doesn't need to be given. Notable  
 617      exception is for a histogram when instead of numer of occurences a  
 618      probability (fraction) of occurences needs to be plotted, in which  
 619      case 'fraction' should be specified. 
 620
